<?php
$t = array();
$t[1] = 'Ya, Seen.';
$t[2] = 'By the wise Qur\'an.';
$t[3] = 'Indeed you, [O Muhammad], are from among the messengers,';
$t[4] = 'On a straight path.';
$t[5] = '[This is] a revelation of the Exalted in Might, the Merciful,';
$t[6] = 'That you may warn a people whose forefathers were not warned, so they are unaware.';
$t[7] = 'Already the word has come into effect upon most of them, so they do not believe.';
$t[8] = 'Indeed, We have put shackles on their necks, and they are to their chins, so they are with heads [kept] aloft.';
$t[9] = 'And We have put before them a barrier and behind them a barrier and covered them, so they do not see.';
$t[10] = 'And it is all the same for them whether you warn them or do not warn them - they will not believe.';
$t[11] = 'You can only warn one who follows the message and fears the Most Merciful unseen. So give him good tidings of forgiveness and noble reward.';
$t[12] = 'Indeed, it is We who bring the dead to life and record what they have put forth and what they left behind, and all things We have enumerated in a clear register.';
$t[13] = 'And present to them an example: the people of the city, when the messengers came to it -';
$t[14] = 'When We sent to them two but they denied them, so We strengthened them with a third, and they said, &quot;Indeed, we are messengers to you.&quot;';
$t[15] = 'They said, &quot;You are not but human beings like us, and the Most Merciful has not revealed a thing. You are only telling lies.&quot;';
$t[16] = 'They said, &quot;Our Lord knows that we are messengers to you,';
$t[17] = 'And we are not responsible except for clear notification.&quot;';
$t[18] = 'They said, &quot;Indeed, we consider you a bad omen. If you do not desist, we will surely stone you, and there will surely touch you, from us, a painful punishment.&quot;';
$t[19] = 'They said, &quot;Your omen is with yourselves. Is it because you were reminded? Rather, you are a transgressing people.&quot;';
$t[20] = 'And there came from the farthest end of the city a man, running. He said, &quot;O my people, follow the messengers.';
$t[21] = 'Follow those who do not ask of you [any] payment, and they are [rightly] guided.';
$t[22] = 'And why should I not worship He who created me and to whom you will be returned?';
$t[23] = 'Should I take other than Him [false] deities [while], if the Most Merciful intends for me some adversity, their intercession will not avail me at all, nor can they save me?';
$t[24] = 'Indeed, I would then be in manifest error.';
$t[25] = 'Indeed, I have believed in your Lord, so listen to me.&quot;';
$t[26] = 'It was said, &quot;Enter Paradise.&quot; He said, &quot;I wish my people could know';
$t[27] = 'Of how my Lord has forgiven me and placed me among the honored.&quot;';
$t[28] = 'And We did not send down upon his people after him any soldiers from the heaven, nor would We have done so.';
$t[29] = 'It was not but one shout, and immediately they were extinguished.';
$t[30] = 'How regretful for the servants. There did not come to them any messenger except that they used to ridicule him.';
$t[31] = 'Have they not considered how many generations We destroyed before them - that they to them will not return?';
$t[32] = 'And indeed, all of them will yet be brought present before Us.';
$t[33] = 'And a sign for them is the dead earth. We have brought it to life and brought forth from it grain, and from it they eat.';
$t[34] = 'And We placed therein gardens of palm trees and grapevines and caused to burst forth therefrom some springs -';
$t[35] = 'That they may eat of His fruit. And their hands have not produced it, so will they not be grateful?';
$t[36] = 'Exalted is He who created all pairs - from what the earth grows and from themselves and from that which they do not know.';
$t[37] = 'And a sign for them is the night. We remove from it [the light of] day, so they are [left] in darkness.';
$t[38] = 'And the sun runs [on course] toward its stopping point. That is the determination of the Exalted in Might, the Knowing.';
$t[39] = 'And the moon - We have determined for it phases, until it returns [appearing] like the old date stalk.';
$t[40] = 'It is not allowable for the sun to reach the moon, nor does the night overtake the day, but each, in an orbit, is swimming.';
$t[41] = 'And a sign for them is that We carried their forefathers in a laden ship.';
$t[42] = 'And We created for them from the likes of it that which they ride.';
$t[43] = 'And if We should will, We could drown them; then no one responding to a cry would there be for them, nor would they be saved';
$t[44] = 'Except as a mercy from Us and provision for a time.';
$t[45] = 'But when it is said to them, &quot;Beware of what is before you and what is behind you; perhaps you will receive mercy... &quot;';
$t[46] = 'And no sign comes to them from the signs of their Lord except that they are from it turning away.';
$t[47] = 'And when it is said to them, &quot;Spend from that which Allah has provided for you,&quot; those who disbelieve say to those who believe, &quot;Should we feed one whom, if Allah had willed, He would have fed? You are not but in clear error.&quot;';
$t[48] = 'And they say, &quot;When is this promise, if you should be truthful?&quot;';
$t[49] = 'They do not await except one blast which will seize them while they are disputing.';
$t[50] = 'And they will not be able [to give] any instruction, nor to their people can they return.';
$t[51] = 'And the Horn will be blown; and at once from the graves to their Lord they will hasten.';
$t[52] = 'They will say, &quot;O woe to us! Who has raised us up from our sleeping place?&quot; [The reply will be], &quot;This is what the Most Merciful had promised, and the messengers told the truth.&quot;';
$t[53] = 'It will not be but one blast, and at once they are all brought present before Us.';
$t[54] = 'So today no soul will be wronged at all, and you will not be recompensed except for what you used to do.';
$t[55] = 'Indeed the companions of Paradise, that Day, will be amused in [joyful] occupation -';
$t[56] = 'They and their spouses - in shade, reclining on adorned couches.';
$t[57] = 'For them therein is fruit, and for them is whatever they request [or wish]';
$t[58] = '[And] &quot;Peace,&quot; a word from a Merciful Lord.';
$t[59] = '[Then He will say], &quot;But stand apart today, you criminals.';
$t[60] = 'Did I not enjoin upon you, O children of Adam, that you not worship Satan - [for] indeed, he is to you a clear enemy -';
$t[61] = 'And that you worship [only] Me? This is a straight path.';
$t[62] = 'And he had already led astray from among you much of creation, so did you not use reason?';
$t[63] = 'This is the Hellfire which you were promised.';
$t[64] = '[Enter to] burn therein today for what you used to deny.&quot;';
$t[65] = 'That Day, We will seal over their mouths, and their hands will speak to Us, and their feet will testify about what they used to earn.';
$t[66] = 'And if We willed, We could have obliterated their eyes, and they would race to [find] the path, and how could they see?';
$t[67] = 'And if We willed, We could have deformed them, [paralyzing them] in their places so they would not be able to proceed, nor could they return.';
$t[68] = 'And he to whom We grant long life We reverse in creation; so will they not understand?';
$t[69] = 'And We did not give Prophet Muhammad, knowledge of poetry, nor is it befitting for him. It is not but a message and a clear Qur\'an';
$t[70] = 'To warn whoever is alive and justify the word against the disbelievers.';
$t[71] = 'Do they not see that We have created for them from what Our hands have made, grazing livestock, and [then] they are their owners?';
$t[72] = 'And We have tamed them for them, so some of them they ride, and some of them they eat.';
$t[73] = 'And for them therein are [other] benefits and drinks, so will they not be grateful?';
$t[74] = 'But they have taken besides Allah [false] deities that perhaps they would be helped.';
$t[75] = 'They are not able to help them, and they [themselves] are for them soldiers in attendance.';
$t[76] = 'So let not their speech grieve you. Indeed, We know what they conceal and what they declare.';
$t[77] = 'Does man not consider that We created him from a [mere] sperm-drop - then at once he is a clear adversary?';
$t[78] = 'And he presents for Us an example and forgets his [own] creation. He says, &quot;Who will give life to bones while they are disintegrated?&quot;';
$t[79] = 'Say, &quot;He will give them life who produced them the first time; and He is, of all creation, Knowing.&quot;';
$t[80] = '[It is] He who made for you from the green tree, fire, and then from it you ignite.';
$t[81] = 'Is not He who created the heavens and the earth Able to create the likes of them? Yes, [it is so]; and He is the Knowing Creator.';
$t[82] = 'His command is only when He intends a thing that He says to it, &quot;Be,&quot; and it is.';
$t[83] = 'So exalted is He in whose hand is the realm of all things, and to Him you will be returned.';
?>